bc: Periodic boundary conditions are imposed in the streamwise and spanwise directions. The temperature is prescribed separately at the hot (Thw) and cold (Tcw) walls, which are both stationary and isothermal with no-slip velocity conditions.
global.ic: Each simulation is initialized with a randomly perturbed parabolic velocity profile. The flow evolves until a statistically steady turbulent state is reached after approximately 10 flow-through times, followed by statistical sampling over an additional 15 flow-through times.
global.description: High-pressure transcritical turbulent channel flow DNS simulations with carbon dioxide (CO2) as the working fluid.  The thermodynamic condition for this case is set as: the reduced pressure (Pb/Pc) = 1.5, the hot-wall reduced temperature (Thw/Tc) = 1.4, and the cold-wall reduced temperature (Tcw/Tc) = 0.8.
global.contributors: Reda El Mansy, Guillem Barea, Lluis Jofre
